<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-58-0223 </DOCNO><TEXT>A class of models for wave propagation in disordered systems (electronsin a random potential or classical waves in a random medium) is considered.The model is defined in terms of a transfer matrix and is specified bypostulating the statistics of matrices corresponding to a single scatteringunit (a multichannel scatterer). It is shown that a certain class ofmodels displays a universal limiting distribution, which is quite insensitiveto the microscopic details of the model and is specified by just oneparameter: the (elastic) mean free path.</TEXT></DOC>